{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "interview-api-collection",
		"name": "Interview API Collection",
		"description": "Postman collection for testing the Interview API endpoints with JWT authentication.\n\n**Authentication Flow:**\n1. Use 'Auth > Login' endpoint to authenticate and get JWT token\n2. The token is automatically extracted and set to the 'jwtToken' collection variable\n3. All protected endpoints will automatically use the token in Authorization header\n\n**Public Endpoints:** Welcome, Register, Login\n**Protected Endpoints:** All other endpoints require JWT token",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Welcome",
			"request": {
				"method": "GET",
				"header": [],
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/welcome",
					"host": [
						"{{baseUrl}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"api",
						"welcome"
					]
				},
				"description": "Welcome endpoint to verify the API is running."
			},
			"response": []
		},
		{
			"name": "Auth",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Register",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"username\": \"newcustomer\",\n    \"password\": \"123456\",\n    \"firstName\": \"John\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n    \"emailAddress\": \"john.doe@example.com\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"auth",
								"register"
							]
						},
						"description": "Public endpoint for customer self-registration. Always creates a user with CUSTOMER role. All fields are required."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Login",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (response.token) {",
									"        pm.collectionVariables.set('jwtToken', response.token);",
									"        console.log('JWT token automatically set to collection variable: jwtToken');",
									"        console.log('Token:', response.token.substring(0, 20) + '...');",
									"    } else {",
									"        console.log('Warning: No token found in response');",
									"    }",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('Login failed. Status:', pm.response.code);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"username\": \"admin\",\n    \"password\": \"123456\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"auth",
								"login"
							]
						},
						"description": "Authenticate user and receive JWT token. The token is automatically extracted from the response and set to the collection variable 'jwtToken' for use in authenticated requests."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Authentication endpoints"
		},
		{
			"name": "Users",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Get All Users",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"users"
							]
						},
						"description": "Retrieve all users from the system. Requires ADMIN role."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get User by ID",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/1",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"users",
								"1"
							]
						},
						"description": "Retrieve a specific user by their ID. Requires ADMIN role."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Current User",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/me",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"users",
								"me"
							]
						},
						"description": "Retrieve the currently authenticated user's details. Available to all authenticated users (ADMIN and CUSTOMER)."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Update Current User",
					"request": {
						"method": "PUT",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"username\": \"updateduser\",\n    \"firstName\": \"John\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n    \"emailAddress\": \"john.doe@example.com\",\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/me",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"users",
								"me"
							]
						},
						"description": "Update the currently authenticated user's own profile. Available to all authenticated users (ADMIN and CUSTOMER). Password can't be updated. Note: userId and role fields are not included in the request."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Delete User",
					"request": {
						"method": "DELETE",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/1",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"users",
								"1"
							]
						},
						"description": "Delete a user by ID. Requires ADMIN role."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Endpoints for managing users"
		},
		{
			"name": "Vehicles",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Create Vehicle",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"brand\": \"Toyota\",\n    \"model\": \"Camry\",\n    \"registrationYear\": 2022,\n    \"licensePlate\": \"ABC-123\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"vehicles"
							]
						},
						"description": "Create a new vehicle. Requires CUSTOMER role. The owner is automatically set from the authenticated user's JWT token. License plate must be unique."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get All Vehicles",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles?page=0&size=10&sortBy=id&sortDir=asc",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"vehicles"
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "brand",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by brand (case-insensitive partial match)",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "model",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by model (case-insensitive partial match)",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "registrationYear",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by exact registration year",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "registrationYearFrom",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by minimum registration year",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "registrationYearTo",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by maximum registration year",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "licensePlate",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by license plate (case-insensitive partial match)",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "ownerId",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Filter by owner ID",
									"disabled": true
								},
								{
									"key": "page",
									"value": "0",
									"description": "Page number (0-indexed)"
								},
								{
									"key": "size",
									"value": "10",
									"description": "Page size (number of items per page)"
								},
								{
									"key": "sortBy",
									"value": "id",
									"description": "Field to sort by (e.g., id, brand, model, registrationYear)"
								},
								{
									"key": "sortDir",
									"value": "asc",
									"description": "Sort direction: asc or desc"
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "Retrieve all vehicles with pagination and filtering. Requires ADMIN role.\n\n**Filtering Parameters:**\n- `brand`: Filter by brand (case-insensitive partial match)\n- `model`: Filter by model (case-insensitive partial match)\n- `registrationYear`: Filter by exact registration year\n- `registrationYearFrom`: Filter by minimum registration year\n- `registrationYearTo`: Filter by maximum registration year\n- `licensePlate`: Filter by license plate (case-insensitive partial match)\n- `ownerId`: Filter by owner ID\n\n**Pagination Parameters:**\n- `page`: Page number (default: 0)\n- `size`: Page size (default: 10)\n- `sortBy`: Field to sort by (default: id)\n- `sortDir`: Sort direction - asc or desc (default: asc)\n\n**Response Format:**\nReturns a paginated response with:\n- `content`: Array of vehicles\n- `page`: Current page number\n- `size`: Page size\n- `totalElements`: Total number of vehicles\n- `totalPages`: Total number of pages\n\n**Example Queries:**\n- `?brand=Toyota&page=0&size=5` - Get first 5 Toyota vehicles\n- `?registrationYearFrom=2020&registrationYearTo=2023&page=0&size=20` - Get vehicles from 2020-2023\n- `?ownerId=2&model=Camry&sortBy=registrationYear&sortDir=desc` - Get Camry vehicles for owner 2, sorted by year descending"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Vehicle by ID",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{jwtToken}}",
								"type": "text"
